Looking at the code, we need to modify the `break_info` method in the `AxisSecondary` ggproto class to properly handle named breaks for discrete scales. Currently, for discrete scales, it gets the breaks but doesn't properly handle their names as labels.

Here's my proposed edit:

```r
break_info = function(self, range, scale) {
  if (self$empty()) return()

  # Test for monotonicity on unexpanded range
  if (!scale$is_discrete()) {
    self$mono_test(scale)
    breaks <- self$breaks
  } else {
    breaks <- scale$map(self$breaks)

    # Add this block to handle named breaks for discrete scales
    if (is.waiver(self$labels) && !is.null(names(breaks))) {
      self$labels <- names(breaks)
    }
  }

  # Get scale's original range before transformation
  transformation <- scale$get_transformation() %||% transform_identity()
  along_range <- seq(range[1], range[2], length.out = self$detail)
  old_range <- transformation$inverse(along_range)

  # Rest of the function remains unchanged
  ...
}
```

Alternatively, a more comprehensive solution would be to modify the `init` method to properly handle this case when initializing the secondary axis:

```r
