Looking at this code, I notice there's an issue with named discrete breaks not being properly handled for secondary axes. When discrete breaks have names, those names should be used as labels by default, just as they would be in primary axes.

Here's my proposed edit to the `AxisSecondary` ggproto object's `init` method:

```r
init = function(self, scale) {
  if (self$empty()) {
    return()
  }
  transform <- self$trans
  if (!is.function(transform)) {
    cli::cli_abort("Transformation for secondary axes must be a function.")
  }
  if (is.derived(self$name) && !is.waiver(scale$name)) self$name <- scale$name
  if (is.derived(self$breaks)) self$breaks <- scale$breaks
  if (is.waiver(self$breaks)) {
    if (scale$is_discrete()) {
      self$breaks <- scale$get_breaks()
    } else {
      breaks <- scale$get_transformation()$breaks
      n_breaks <- scale$n.breaks
      if (!is.null(n_breaks) && "n" %in% fn_fmls_names(breaks)) {
        self$breaks <- function(x) breaks(x, n = n_breaks)
      } else {
        self$breaks <- breaks
      }
    }
  }
  if (is.derived(self$labels)) {
    self$labels <- scale$labels
  } else if (is.waiver(self$labels) && scale$is_discrete()) {
    # For discrete scales, if breaks have names and labels is a waiver,
    # use the break names as labels
    breaks <- if (is.function(self$breaks)) {
      self$breaks(scale$get_limits())
    } else {
      self$breaks
    }
    if (!is.null(breaks) && !is.waiver(breaks) && !is.null(names(breaks))) {
      self$labels <- names(breaks)
    }
  }
  if (is.derived(self$guide)) self$guide <- scale$guide
}
```

This change ensures that when the secondary axis is associated with a discrete scale and the breaks have names, those names will be used as labels by default (when `labels = waiver()`). This maintains consistency with how primary axes handle named discrete breaks.

